						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, Achalēśvara shrine, Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 2: 987 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription belongs to the reign of Rājakēsarivarman evidently that of Rājarāja I. It records a gift of two silver vessels in which offerings were to be made to god Tiruvaraneṟi-Āḻvār by Uḍaiyapirāṭṭiyār Sembiyaṉ-Mahādēviyār for the merit of Uttamachōḷa. She sent these vessels to the temple under the supervision of (her) bodyguard Nīlaṉ Mādēvaṉ.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIII No. 1.</p>						

						</summary>
